# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 02-hyv3-mtp-tools.patch — HY_V3 second-stage: MTP + thinking/tool parser
#
# Base        : 19bba67c1 WITH 01-hyv3-arch.patch already applied.
#               (This patch depends on 01; apply 01 first, then this one.)
#
# PROVENANCE / ATTRIBUTION
#   Original work, not derived from the GrahLnn patch.
#
# WHAT IT ADDS (two independent features)
#   1. MTP / NextN self-speculative decoding for hy_v3
#      - loads the extra decoder block (HF model.layers.<n_hidden>, e.g. layer 80)
#        as a NextN head; adds graph_mtp mirroring vLLM HYV3MultiTokenPredictorLayer.
#      - gated purely by hparams.n_layer_nextn: pre-MTP gguf (key absent) load & run
#        BYTE-FOR-BYTE unchanged. Enable at runtime with: --spec-type draft-mtp
#      - conversion: emit nextn_predict_layers; convert_hf_to_gguf.py --no-mtp drops
#        the head (for checkpoints that carry no MTP weights).
#   2. hy_v3 thinking + tool-call parser (common/chat.cpp)
#      - <think{sfx}>...</think{sfx}> reasoning + key/value-split tagged tool calls
#        (<tool_call{sfx}>name<tool_sep{sfx}><arg_key..><arg_value..>). PEG-native.
#      - per-tokenizer special-token suffix (e.g. ":opensource" or empty) is
#        EXTRACTED from the chat template at runtime, never hard-coded.
#
# APPLY (after 01)
#   git apply 02-hyv3-mtp-tools.patch
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
